111.--20. illam usque ad talos demissam purpuram3 viz. the toga praetexta (purple-edged toga) of the curule magistrate, which was not worn by the quaestor or lower officials, nor by plebeian magistrates such as the tribunes, none of whom enjoyed the curule chair. It is to be observed that the sense of the passage requires us to refer these words to a time subsequent (postea, 1. 17) to Quinctius’ tribunate. It is to be supposed that Quinctius after his tribunate rose ‘ to a higher place‚' to the curule aedile- ship or praetorship. (So Cic. derides Vatinius for having as tribune bought a praetexta to be ready against the aedileship which never came to him, z‘n Vatin. ἓ 16).
